# üêû bug report

### Affected Package
This issue is caused by @angular/compiler more specifically:

- [line 39 - util.ts]{https://github.com/angular/angular/blob/88b0985bad498f2fdd6bc8846279f63ed3acb205/packages/compiler/src/util.ts#L39) - checks to see if an object is a map of  strings. Because the proxy was created as ```new Proxy({}, ...```
- the proxy matches and is then replaced by a new object by ```visitor.visitStringMap```

### Is this a regression?
I have had this issue in multiple angular releases

### Description
If you use a proxy object as the provided value in a unit test (this is done by some mocking frameworks like ts-mockito) the proxy is removed when the test runs.

In the reproduction I made a simple proxy manually that returns the mocked method:
<pre><code>
    const mockedSomeService = new Proxy({} as SomeService, {
      get: (target, prop) => {
        if (prop === "returnSomething") {
          return () => "mocked something";
        } else {
          return target[prop];
        }
      },
    });
</code></pre>

There are some workarounds (granted it isn't obvious), the first option is to create some kind of class other than a generic object {}:
<pre><code>
    const mockedSomeService = new Proxy(new AnyClass() as SomeService, {
    ...
</code></pre>

the other is to use a factory when injecting
<pre><code>
    providers: [{ provide: SomeService, useFactory: () => mockedSomeService }],
    // instead of
    // providers: [{ provide: SomeService, useValue: mockedSomeService }], 
</code></pre>

## üî¨ Minimal Reproduction
I can't make a reproduction on stackblitz since the error occurs inside test execution, here is a repo on GitHub: https://github.com/DW8Reaper/TestBed-proxy-removal-reproduction

## üî• Exception or Error
When you run the test for app.component.spec.ts the test fails:
<pre><code>
